12. Difference Between Strategy and Factory

Strategy	Factory

Changes behavior	Creates objects
Focus on algorithm	Focus on object creation
Runtime behavior selection	Runtime object creation


Example:

Factory

PaymentFactory.Create("UPI");

creates object.

Strategy

payment.Pay();

executes behavior.

Factory creates.

Strategy behaves.


